MARKET STRUCTURE CONTEXT (Smart Money Concepts)
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

STRUCTURE DEFINITIONS

- Break of Structure (BOS) : Price closes beyond the most recent swing high (bullish) or swing low (bearish) → trend continuation signal
- Change of Character (CHoCH): Price breaks the opposing swing level → first sign of trend reversal
- Order Block (OB) : The last opposing candle before an impulsive move; treat as institutional S/R
• Bullish OB = last bearish candle before strong rally (demand zone)
• Bearish OB = last bullish candle before strong drop (supply zone)
- Fair Value Gap (FVG) : 3-candle imbalance where middle candle body doesn't overlap with candle 1 & 3 wicks → price tends to return and fill

OB & FVG IDENTIFICATION RULES
✅ Valid OB must precede an impulsive move that causes BOS or CHoCH
✅ OB zone = full candle range (high to low of the identified candle)
✅ FVG must be created by an impulsive move (3+ consecutive directional candles)
✅ Unmitigated OB/FVG = price has NOT returned to the zone yet → highest probability
✅ Prioritize OBs that align with EMA 50/200 dynamic S/R
❌ OBs in the middle of a range with no impulsive follow-through = invalid
❌ FVGs already filled/mitigated = no longer active

TIMEFRAME PRIORITY FOR SMC
• 4H / 1H : Identify key OBs and FVGs for intraday bias
• 15M / 5M : Refine entry within the 4H/1H OB or FVG zone

