LIQUIDITY ZONES & SWEEP DETECTION
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

LIQUIDITY POOL TYPES

1. Equal Highs (EQH) : 2+ swing highs at approximately the same price → buy-side liquidity
2. Equal Lows (EQL) : 2+ swing lows at approximately the same price → sell-side liquidity
3. Trendline Liquidity : Obvious trendline with 3+ touches → stops clustered beyond the trendline
4. Session Highs/Lows : Previous session's high/low act as liquidity targets

SWEEP DETECTION RULES
✅ A liquidity sweep occurs when price WICKS BEYOND a liquidity level but CLOSES BACK inside
✅ The sweep candle should show clear rejection (long wick, small body = Pin Bar / Hammer)
✅ Volume spike on the sweep candle confirms institutional participation
✅ A sweep followed by a BOS in the opposite direction = HIGH-PROBABILITY reversal entry

SWEEP TRADING PROTOCOL

1. Identify liquidity pool (EQH/EQL/trendline)
2. Wait for price to sweep beyond → DO NOT enter on the sweep candle
3. Look for rejection candle (Tier-1 pattern) on the NEXT candle after the sweep
4. Entry on confirmation candle CLOSE, SL beyond the sweep wick
5. Target: opposite liquidity pool or unmitigated OB/FVG

⚠️ BTC-SPECIFIC NOTE: BTC frequently sweeps Asian session highs/lows during London open,
and London session highs/lows during NY open. Use this as a timing filter.

