━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

Counter-trend trades are ONLY permitted when ALL of the following conditions are met:

MANDATORY REQUIREMENTS (ALL must be ✅)
☐ 1. Strong RSI Divergence (🔴 grade) — Regular Divergence on 1H or 4H
☐ 2. Tier-1 candlestick pattern at a SIGNIFICANT S/R level (fractal, OB, round number)
☐ 3. Minimum R:R upgraded to 1:4 (not 1:3)
☐ 4. Position size reduced to 0.5% of capital ($15 risk instead of $30)
☐ 5. Price has reached an extreme level (RSI < 20 or RSI > 80 on entry TF)

ADDITIONAL FILTERS
✅ Liquidity sweep occurred at the level → swept stops, now reversing
✅ MACD histogram shows momentum exhaustion (declining histogram bars)
✅ Funding rate is extreme in the trend direction (squeeze potential)
✅ At least 2/5 macro-correlated assets support the reversal

COUNTER-TREND EXECUTION PROTOCOL
• Use OPTION A (Single Entry) only — no scaling into counter-trend trades
• Set TP at the nearest significant S/R level (conservative target)
• Trail SL aggressively — move to breakeven after 1:1 R:R is reached
• If trade does not trigger within 3 candles of signal → invalidate and cancel

⚠️ GOLDEN RULE: If in doubt, DO NOT take a counter-trend trade.
It is always safer to wait for a trend-aligned setup.

